(44, 20, 33, 4, 16, 15, 15, 'coveted no man’s silver, or gold', 'Integrity in Leadership', 'Both passages emphasize the integrity of leaders who refuse personal gain. Acts 20:33 highlights the absence of covetousness, while Numbers 16:15 underscores Moses'' refusal of offerings, reinforcing the theme of righteous leadership.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
